===Etymology===
From {{term|Turkey|lang=en}}. The [[guinea fowl]] ({{term|Numida meleagris|lang=mul}}), native to Africa, was imported to Europe by ''[[Turkey merchant]]s''. The larger northern American bird {{term|Meleagris gallopavo|lang=mul}}, thought to resemble the guinea fowl, was brought to Spain by [[conquistador]]s in 1523; from there it was introduced to northern Africa, at the time under [[Ottoman]] rule, and then via the [[Middle East]] back into Europe.

